# Security Rules — Omnix Runtime

Source: `packages/core/standards/security.md`

- Never commit secrets. Rotate any secret that touched a repo.
- Parameterized queries always. No string concatenation into SQL/shell/HTML.
- Argon2id (or bcrypt ≥12) for passwords.
- HttpOnly + Secure + SameSite cookies. Or short-lived JWT + refresh.
- Authorization on every endpoint — not just the gateway.
- CSRF tokens on state-changing form submissions.
- CSP, X-Content-Type-Options, X-Frame-Options headers set.
- Never log secrets, full PII, or full request bodies of sensitive endpoints.
- Every security incident: postmortem + prevention rule in `03-ERRORS/anti-patterns.md`.
